
[1]attemper

   ATTEM'PER, v.t. [L. attempero, of ad and tempero, to temper, mix, or
   moderate. See Temper.]

   1. To reduce, modify or moderate by mixture; as, to attemper heat by a
   cooling mixture, or spirit by diluting it with water.

   2. To soften, mollify or moderate; as, to attemper rigid justice with
   clemency.

   3. To mix in just proportion; to regulate; as, a mind well attempered
   with kindness and justice.

   4. To accommodate; to fit or make suitable.

   Arts attempered to the lyre.
